x4freetext: TANDEM VAN DE GRAAFF AT THE CENTRE D`ETUDES
THE PROTON BEAM WAS PULSED AND BUNCHED INTO
AVERAGE CURRENT  2 MICRO AMPS, INCIDENT ON A THIN
99.8 PERCENT  LI-7 TARGET EVAPOURATED ON A 1MM
.CYLINDRICAL AT 0 DEG TO PROTON BEAM AXIS AT 10.3CM
FROM THE TARGET. ALL SAMPLES WERE 1.5CM DIAMETER
4 DETECTOR TIME OF FLIGHT. FOR DETAILS SEE
SCINTILLATORS OPTICALLY COUPLED TO AN XP-1040
FLIGHT PATH FROM SAMPLE TO DETECTOR WAS 10METERS.
OVERALL ENERGY RESOLUTION OF SCATTERED NEUTRONS
WAS LESS THAN 28KEV. PULSE SHAPE DISCRIMINATION
WAS USED TO REGECT GAMMA PULSES.
REACTIONS ON LI-7. THIS NORMALISATION WAS
CONSISTENT WITH AN AUXILIARY NEUTRON DETECTOR USED
IN THE TOF MODE TO ONE PERCENT.
.YIELDS CORRECTED FOR ANISOTROPY EFFECTS IN THE
NEUTRON FLUX AND FINITE SIZE EFFECTS IN THE SAMPLE,
EFFECTS. ANALYTICAL METHOD OF KINNEY USED.
EFFICIENCY AND SAMPLE CORRECTIONS ALL ADDED QUADRATI
